							"score": 5,
							"reviewDescription": "This game is excellent - imagine a full game based around the shadow puzzles from Resident Evil 7 wrapped up in a story book. It runs great on Quest 2, looks good and the puzzles are just difficult enough to be challenging without ever becoming frustrating. There are even extra challenges for those who solve all of the \"main quest\" puzzles which lead to new rooms filled with even harder challenges.\n\nMy only (very small) criticism is that it can be difficult to follow the story at times since you can play most of the levels in whatever order you'd like. I got the impression that there is an intended order that I was definitely not following which made things a bit disjointed story wise, but I had so much fun exploring and solving the shadow puzzles that it didn't really matter much.",
